fields.description:
We are getting an Error Message in Greenhopper when trying to log work "Unable to log work". I cant find anything about this error message anywhere on the web, Logging work through the normal Jira interface and through the TEMPO Plugin works. What is the issue in Greenhopper? Is there a way to find out were and why this error gets thrown ?
{noformat}
WARNING: Parameters: Invalid chunk ignored.
2010-06-03 16:37:10,219 TP-Processor9 ERROR agrunewald 997x37765x1 1pclvj0 10.125.1.14 /secure/GHLogWork.jspa [greenhopper.jira.actions.CardBoardAction] java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: "7.5"
{noformat}

It seems as if Greenhopper is doing something with our hours per workday. Probably to parse how many hours 1d is. We set up 7.5h for our workday. Jira 4.1 supports fractions in the workday and I would assume Greenhopper has problems with that. I know that this feature is new for Jira 4.1

{panel:title=Atlassian Status as of 12 March 2012| borderStyle=solid| borderColor=#ccc| titleBGColor=#49BD5F| bgColor=#E7F4FA}
We understand that the use of labels for Epics is not adequate to model the relationships between items in an Agile backlog. 

We have worked with the JIRA team to implement performant issue links. We can now use this form of issue relationship instead of labels. 

At this stage, we have not integrated this specific functionality in GreenHopper, though it can be used. In the future we will use it to model Epics (and more generally the breakdown of higher level stories in to smaller ones) in the GreenHopper Rapid Board. 
{panel}
